apt-get install ncurses-dev

scratch the pcre stuff; look at lua patterns instead.

added perl regex around v 1.87

recast killbuffer to be a linked list of lines.  killregion then just moves a 
region to the killbuffer.  yank could add a linked list of lines in at the 
current point.  kill lines unlinks a line from the active buffer, and links 
it into the killbuffer.  region structure probably becomes a 
(first line/offset, last line/offset, number of chars) structure.  the 
tricky part is at the line boundaries, because the insert may be into the 
interior of an existing line.

A quick fix was to pre-expand the kill buffer size if the size of the region 
to be killed was large -- massive improvement. (20060329)

Also may want indefinitely large number of kill buffers.  (in lua, a variable
that is a region)
